metadata.title: Beechcraft Bonanza
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Bonanza V35 Series Variants
V35 is a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
V35 was produced from 1966 to 1967.
V35 was fitted with a single-piece windshield.
V35 was powered by an IO-520-B engine.
V35 was optionally available with a 285 hp (213 kW) turbocharged TSIO-520-D engine.
V35 with the turbocharged engine was designated as V35-TC.
873 V35 aircraft were built.
79 of the 873 V35 aircraft were V35-TC models.
V35A is a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
V35A was produced from 1968 to 1969.
V35A was fitted with a revised windshield.
V35A was powered by an IO-520-B engine.
V35A was optionally available with a turbocharged TSIO-520-D engine.
V35A with the turbocharged engine was designated as V35A-TC.
470 V35A aircraft were built.
46 of the 470 V35A aircraft were V35A-TC models.
V35B is a variant of the Beechcraft Bonanza.
V35B was produced from 1970 to 1982.
V35B initially had minor improvements over the V35A.
V35B had a major internal redesign in 1972.
V35B received a 24-volt electrical system in 1978.
V35B was normally powered by an IO-520B engine.
V35B was available with an optional TSIO-520-D engine until 1971.
V35B with the turbocharged engine was designated as V35TC.
1335 V35B aircraft were built.
7 of the 1335 V35B aircraft were V35TC models.

text:
V35
(19661967) Fitted with single-piece windshield, powered by IO-520-B or optional 285 hp (213 kW) turbocharged TSIO-520-D engine (as V35-TC). 873 built, including 79 V35-TCs.
V35A
(19681969) Fitted with revised windshield, powered by IO-520-B or by optional turbocharged TSIO-520-D engine (as V35A-TC), 470 built, including 46 V35A-TCs.
V35B
(19701982) Initially with minor improvements over V35A, but had major internal redesign in 1972, and 24-volt electrical system in 1978. Normally powered by IO-520B, but available with optional TSIO-520-D (as V35TC) until 1971. 1335 built, including 7 V35TCs.
